<br>
Gimily and Beaon - You're right.. It IS your $10 bucks a month to play your character as you see fit. But just remember - it doesn't take much to be nice - maybe patience and a little bit of effort.  I'll be honest - it's not cheap helping others. But people don't forget when someone is nice to them.  <br>
<br>
Being a potatohead is cheap and easy - ANYONE can do THAT.<br>
<br>
For those complaining about those &quot;but-it-costs-ME-mana-to-buff/heal/port-YOU&quot; situations... ask that requestor to help you kill your next critter.  That way they get a buff, you get easy experience for your time and you both walk away a winner.  And.. as a bonus... during downtime, you get to exchange pleasantries and a little bit of knowledge about each other.<br>
<br>
For those who are asking for buffs, be creative.  Start working on your baking or brewing skills.  Concoct a few stacks of stat bonus food/drink and hand it to the person to whom you are begging for assistance.  Lots of folks don't know about stat foods and welcome not only your personal effort but the newfound knowledge regarding your trade skills! Everyone has money and no one needs that 2 plat you're offering for SoW.  But hand that player something they might not be able to get on their own and you leave them impressed as all heck.   Hey, if you're too lazy to be THIS creative, then you don't really deserve the buffs you are looking for.<br>
<br>
Remember - There's always a solution. <br>
<br>
&quot;No&quot; is a perfectly viable answer to someone's request for help... but in my opinion, it's definitely not the best answer.<br>
<br>
Your Friendly Neighborhood Rezzer,<br>
Dak <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=281.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=281.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=281.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=281.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=281.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=281.topic&start=121&stop=121>7</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=281.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=281.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=281.topic&index=80><img src=http://quellious-collective.com/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=281.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.threadControl?topicID=281.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTop